summary:
* Requests the Emergency Relief Coordinator to report on implementation and impediments to humanitarian aid delivery.

* Requests enhanced cooperation and information sharing between the Monitoring Group and humanitarian organizations.

* Exempts certain supplies and assistance for the UN Political Office for Somalia and humanitarian use from arms embargoes.

* Extends the mandate of the Monitoring Group until 25 August 2013, with tasks including:

  - Monitoring implementation of sanctions
  - Reporting on violations
  - Investigating seaport operations and revenue generation for Al-Shabaab
  - Investigating activities generating revenues for arms embargoes violations
  - Refining and updating information on individuals and entities engaging in acts subject to sanctions.
The Security Council:

Appoints a Monitoring Group pursuant to previous resolutions;

The Monitoring Group is tasked to:
- Work closely with the Committee on recommendations to improve compliance with Somalia and Eritrea arms embargoes (j);
- Identify areas to strengthen States' capacities in the region to implement the embargoes (k);
- Provide a midterm briefing within six months and monthly progress reports to the Committee (l);
- Submit two final reports, one on Somalia and one on Eritrea, no later than thirty days prior to the termination of its mandate (m);

Requests the Secretary-General to make necessary financial arrangements to support the Monitoring Group (14);

Requests the Committee to consider the Monitoring Group's recommendations and suggest ways to improve implementation and compliance with the embargoes (15);

Urges all parties and States to cooperate with the Monitoring Group, ensure its safety, and provide unhindered access to persons, documents, and sites (16);

Decides to remain actively seized of the matter (17).
